 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uabru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/9/02 1:02:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27062.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What makes Druids &quot;Over Balanced&quot; prior to 50?</span><hr size=1> Read the petition for more (complete) answers to your question.<br>
<br>
One simple non-raid related answer is that prior to 50, no mobs summon you, which facilitates a druid's most common exping activity, kiting.  So, basically, at 50+, suddenly you can't kite mobs that are your level.  Yeah, yeah, I know, a lot of druids never did try to kill mobs their own level -- those druid are just exp-grinders.  Personally, I always liked the challenge of killing as tough a mob as I reasonably could, and still trying to get my exp bar to move upwards. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=126501">Abru</a>, Elder Hierophant on The Nameless,  <a href="http://www.legacyofsteel.net/index.shtml" target=_top>Legacy of Steel</a>, <a href="mailto:AbruEQ@hotmail.com">AbruEQ@hotmail.com</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rtfm>rtfm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/9/02 1:10:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27062.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Bards Kite.<br>
